    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv40-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepts the validation evidence as sufficient to support the COU2 hemolysis prediction claim. All assessed credibility factors meet or approach required levels. The solver version used in validation (ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2) is considered effectively equivalent to the released model of record (ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7); the single patch between rc2 and release addressed only turbulence wall-function residual tolerance and is judged non-material to the hemolysis QoI. Re-execution of validation runs under the released binary was not performed and is not deemed necessary. Unassessed factors (model inputs, test samples, equivalency of input parameters) are acknowledged as epistemic gaps but are accepted under the Low assurance level designation for this assessment cycle.",
